It's delicious.

248
00:14:40,913 --> 00:14:43,781
I hear delicious,
but I see disappointed.

249
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:48,847
It's not...

250
00:14:49,455 --> 00:14:51,447
the chicken, it's my patient.

251
00:14:51,958 --> 00:14:53,358
We fixed his airway,

252
00:14:53,426 --> 00:14:55,861
and he can breathe
without the trach now.

253
00:14:56,362 --> 00:14:59,025
- That's fantastic.
- But he still can't talk.

254
00:14:59,298 --> 00:15:01,858
He can talk.
He just does it with his hands.

255
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:05,393
Mm. But only with people
who can also sign,

256
00:15:05,471 --> 00:15:07,804
and they have to be looking at him,
and...

257
00:15:07,907 --> 00:15:09,773
Could you do
a cadaveric larynx transplant?

258
00:15:09,876 --> 00:15:11,777
- No.
- I've heard that's worked

259
00:15:11,878 --> 00:15:15,371
- for some throat cancer patients.
- No. Dr. Lim ruled that out years ago.

260
00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:18,885
The risk of tissue rejection
is too great in a child his age.

261
00:15:18,951 --> 00:15:21,614
- Well, could you wait till he's older?
- No!

262
00:15:23,589 --> 00:15:27,822
If he doesn't learn to speak soon,
he'll never be able to.

263
00:15:28,961 --> 00:15:29,961
Okay.

264
00:15:33,766 --> 00:15:36,326
I need to do some reading.

265
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:40,269
Come on, Shaun,
at least eat something first.

266
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:45,071
No, I'm hungry,
but I will do the reading first.

267
00:16:33,559 --> 00:16:34,652
You're in early.

268
00:16:36,262 --> 00:16:37,262
What's the haps?

269
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,993
Are you serious?

270
00:16:42,068 --> 00:16:45,300
I didn't even know Michelle Obama
was in SEAL Team Six.

271
00:16:47,907 --> 00:16:51,867
You noticed how Glassy grinds
his teeth listening to someone talk?

272
00:16:51,978 --> 00:16:54,709
- It's like a cow chewing on her...
- You never used to do that.

273
00:16:54,981 --> 00:16:55,981
Do what?

274
00:16:56,415 --> 00:16:58,043
Eat food off my plate.

275
00:16:58,684 --> 00:17:01,518
I used to work full-time at a place
with private chefs.

276
00:17:01,587 --> 00:17:03,317
Now I work part-time in a place

277
00:17:03,389 --> 00:17:05,324
with hard-boiled eggs
in a vending machine.

278
00:17:05,391 --> 00:17:08,054
She said it's like you're peeing
on my leg.

279
00:17:09,829 --> 00:17:11,195
Expand on that.

280
00:17:11,564 --> 00:17:14,864
Morgan thinks your body language says

281
00:17:14,934 --> 00:17:17,870
you're trying to assert
your dominance over Carly.

282
00:17:17,937 --> 00:17:19,906
Morgan is one twisted beyotch.

283
00:17:20,172 --> 00:17:21,172
Is she right?

284
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,240
No.

285
00:17:22,441 --> 00:17:23,807
Not even close.

286
00:17:24,744 --> 00:17:28,078
I promise you my voice
and body language

287
00:17:28,180 --> 00:17:29,944
are communicating the same thing,

288
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:34,453
which is pure,
non-threatening, platonic friendship.

289
00:17:37,456 --> 00:17:38,617
Shaun?

290
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:42,061
He also snores.

291
00:17:42,128 --> 00:17:44,393
- Really loud.
- Glassman?

292
00:17:44,463 --> 00:17:46,591
Oh. I have to go.

293
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:54,239
Okay.

294
00:18:01,047 --> 00:18:03,243
Hmm. Incision sites look good,

295
00:18:03,549 --> 00:18:07,384
and skin and tissue grafts appear
to be taking hold nicely.

296
00:18:07,787 --> 00:18:10,916
We were able to reattach
your bicep muscle and tendon.

297
00:18:10,990 --> 00:18:12,356
That's good to hear.

298
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:13,484
Can you lift your arm?

299
00:18:18,931 --> 00:18:20,456
No, I can't.

300
00:18:21,233 --> 00:18:22,861
Because it hurts too much?

301
00:18:23,936 --> 00:18:25,302
It doesn't hurt at all.

302
00:18:27,173 --> 00:18:29,574
I figured that was
because of the meds.

303
00:18:34,747 --> 00:18:35,747
You feel that?

304
00:18:37,283 --> 00:18:38,283
No.

305
00:18:46,192 --> 00:18:48,127
Vocal cords aren't the only way

306
00:18:48,194 --> 00:18:51,028
